T6040 J614s protected NVMe queue diagnostic, 2026-07-14
========================================================

Target: 14-inch M4 Pro, T6040/J614s, Mac16,8
Policy: staged nvme modules; no namespace command or user-storage access

Read-only m1n1 guarded-state snapshot before the Linux attempt:

  CurrentEL=0x8
  AIDR_EL1=0xd168699696
  SPRR_CONFIG_EL1=0x0
  GXF_CONFIG_EL1=0x0
  GXF_STATUS_EL1=0x0
  GXF_ENTER_EL1=SYNC exception
  GXF_ABORT_EL1=SYNC exception

Relevant Linux current-boot trace:

  nvme-apple 40dcc0000.nvme: trace: before ANS CPU control read
  apple-sart 40dc50000.iommu: trace: CoastGuard activate begin
  apple-sart 40dc50000.iommu: trace: CoastGuard activate complete
  apple-sart 40dc50000.iommu: trace: SART entry scan begin
  apple-sart 40dc50000.iommu: trace: SART entry scan complete
  nvme-apple 40dcc0000.nvme: trace: ANS RTKit boot returned
  nvme-apple 40dcc0000.nvme: trace: before ANS boot status read
  nvme-apple 40dcc0000.nvme: trace: ANS boot status ready
  nvme-apple 40dcc0000.nvme: trace: before linear queue and NVMMU setup
  nvme-apple 40dcc0000.nvme: trace: preserving firmware-owned linear queue and NVMMU setup
  nvme-apple 40dcc0000.nvme: trace: linear queue and NVMMU setup complete
  nvme-apple 40dcc0000.nvme: trace: before protected admin queue setup
  Call trace:

No "protected admin queue setup returned" marker appeared. The sole CPU hung
inside Apple GENTER (`.inst 0x00201420`) while invoking the kernelcache-derived
service-6 op-0/op-4 sequence. Shell input echoed but did not execute. The
watchdog warm-reset the machine, and m1n1 returned to "Running proxy".

Conclusion: the macOS NVMe SPTM ABI is decoded correctly enough to reproduce
its entry sequence, but raw boot has no usable guarded entry. Do not repeat
this call unchanged and do not substitute direct secure-BAR writes.
